    {
        "content": "<p>I am afraid that the leap is quite significant. You have proven that A1 is countable, A1 + A2 is countable, A1 + A2 + A3 is countable, ... so you could hope that when this infinite nested sequence of sets is countable, the full union is \"trivially\" countable too. Unfortunatelly, instead of being trivial, it translates back to the original problem -- you are taking an union of infinitely many countable sets, and you want the union to be countable.</p>",
